MENINGOCOCCAL VACCINE NEED (04)
===============================
[We continue to receive helpful suggestions and information regarding travel
to Saudi Arabia. We are posting two more (below) and then cutting this
string. I believe we have enough information now and we thank those who have
been so helpful.-- Mod CHC]
[see
Meningococcal vaccine need: RFI 970304153522
Meningococcal vaccine need (02) 970305125913
Meningococcal vaccine need during Hajj (03) 970304173207]
[1]
Date: Wed, 05 Mar 1997 17:19:19 -0800
From: David Dassey <ddassey@dhs.co.la.ca.us>
The Centers for Disease Control's "Summary of Health Information for
International Travel", commonly known as the Blue Sheet, recently has
provided an update of vaccination requirements for travel to Saudi Arabia for
the upcoming pilgrimage to Mecca. There are also requirements for yellow
fever and diphtheria vaccination, depending on country of origin and route of
travel.
The statement is reprinted from the WHO Weekly Epidemiologic Record, No. 50,
13 Dec 96. The Blue Sheet is also available on the CDC website for those
with such access. The entire CDC "Health Information for International
Travel" (so-called Yellow Book) is reached at http://www.cdc.gov/ . Choose
the Travelers' Health menu.
---
David E. Dassey, MD
Acute Communicable Disease Control
Dept. Health Services, County of Los Angeles
California, USA
